The paper discusses error-correcting codes and their applications in computational complexity theory and cryptography. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the combinatorial aspects of error-correcting codes, it is less likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics sub-category.
